<section xml:id="cansas1d_documentation-element-SASdata" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    version="5.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
    <title>SAStransmission_spectrum element</title>
    <itemizedlist mark="opencircle">
        <listitem>
            <indexterm significance="preferred">
                <primary>element</primary>
                <secondary>SAStransmission_spectrum</secondary>
            </indexterm>
            <para> parent: <link xlink:href="#cansas1d_documentation-element-SASentry"
                ><literal>SASentry</literal></link>
            </para>
        </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <figure>
        <title>The SAStransmission_spectrum element</title>
        <mediaobject>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="../../graphics/11-SAStransmission_spectrum.png" width="200pt" scalefit="1"/>
            </imageobject>
            <textobject>
                <phrase>cansas1d-v1-11-SAStransmission_spectrum.png</phrase>
            </textobject>
            <caption>
                <para>The SAStransmission_spectrum element</para>
            </caption>
        </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>The <literal>SAStransmission_spectrum</literal> element has a 
        <literal>name</literal> attribute to identify what type of spectrum
        is being described.  It is expected that this value will take either 
        of these two values:
        <table orient="port" role="small">
            <title/>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="15*"/>
                <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="15*"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>value</entry>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>meaning</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry><literal>sample</literal></entry>
                        <entry>measurement with the sample and container</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry><literal>can</literal></entry>
                        <entry>measurement with just the container</entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </para>
    <section>
        <title>SAStransmission_spectrum</title>
        <table orient="port" role="small">
            <title/>
            <tgroup cols="5">
                <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="15*"/>
                <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="15*"/>
                <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="10*"/>
                <colspec colname="c4" colwidth="30*"/>
                <colspec colname="c5" colwidth="30*"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>Name</entry>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>Type</entry>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>Occurrence</entry>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>Description</entry>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>Attributes</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <literal>Tdata</literal>
                            <indexterm>
                                <primary>element</primary>
                                <secondary>Tdata</secondary>
                            </indexterm>
                        </entry>
                        <entry> container </entry>
                        <entry> [1..inf] </entry>
                        <entry> Tdata describes a single transmission spectrum data point. </entry>
                        <entry/>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Tdata</title>
        <table orient="port" role="small">
            <title/>
            <tgroup cols="5">
                <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="15*"/>
                <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="15*"/>
                <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="10*"/>
                <colspec colname="c4" colwidth="30*"/>
                <colspec colname="c5" colwidth="30*"/>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>Name</entry>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>Type</entry>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>Occurrence</entry>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>Description</entry>
                        <entry><?dblatex bgcolor="[gray]{0.8}"?>Attributes</entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <literal>Lambda</literal>
                                <indexterm>
                                    <primary>element</primary>
                                    <secondary>Lambda</secondary>
                                </indexterm>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry> floating-point number </entry>
                        <entry> [1..1] </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                Wavelength of the radiation bin. 
                                The <literal>unit</literal> attribute is required. See <link
                                    xlink:href="#cansas1d_documentation-rules">rules for
                                    units</link>
                                for acceptable values. Either
                                <literal>A</literal> or <literal>nm</literal> are
                                typical. </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry><literal>unit={unit}</literal></entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <literal>T</literal>
                                <indexterm>
                                    <primary>element</primary>
                                    <secondary>T</secondary>
                                </indexterm>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry> floating-point number </entry>
                        <entry> [1..1] </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para> Transmission value (I/Io). </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry><literal>unit={unit}</literal></entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <literal>Tdev</literal>
                                <indexterm>
                                    <primary>element</primary>
                                    <secondary>Idev</secondary>
                                </indexterm>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry> floating-point number </entry>
                        <entry> [0..1] </entry>
                        <entry> Estimated uncertainty (usually standard deviation) of <literal>T</literal>.
                            The <literal>unit</literal> attribute is required. See
                                <link xlink:href="#cansas1d_documentation-rules">rules for
                                units</link> for acceptable values. One
                            possibility might be <literal>1/cm</literal>. </entry>
                        <entry><literal>unit={unit}</literal></entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <link xlink:href="#cansas1d_documentation-element-any"
                                ><literal>{any}</literal></link>
                            <indexterm>
                                <primary>element</primary>
                                <secondary>&lt;any&gt;</secondary>
                            </indexterm>
                        </entry>
                        <entry> container </entry>
                        <entry> [0..inf] </entry>
                        <entry> Any element(s) not defined in the cansas1d/1.1 standard can be
                            placed at this point. 
                            See <link xlink:href="#cansas1d_documentation-element-any"
                                ><literal>{any}</literal></link>
                            for more details. </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <link
                                    xlink:href="#cansas1d_documentation-element-any"
                                    ><literal>xmlns:{foreign-prefix}={foreign-namespace}</literal></link>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <note>
            <para> When an optional element 
                (<literal>Tdev</literal>) 
                is used, it must be given in
                every <literal>Tdata</literal> within the 
                enclosing <literal>SAStransmission_spectrum</literal>. </para>
        </note>
    </section>
</section>
